Dec 9 2008 	Decent Hotel	We stayed at the Wall Street Inn starting the Friday after Thanksgiving. I was pleasantly surprised. The rooms are small, but to be expected in NYC, but they were always clean as was the hotel as a whole. The location is just off Wall Street, hence the name, and is close to various subway stations making it easy to get anywhere in the city. (Although, many of the subway stations in that area had limited availability over the weekend while we were there, so be sure to check the NYC tranisit site before heading to the subway station). The location was generally quiet, especially on the weekend, which can be a good thing for sleeping, but not the best for finding stuff to do. Most of the bars in the area were &quot;corner&quot; type bars, great for stopping by for a quick drink before heading out to one of New York's more exciting neighborhoods. It is also close to the free Staten Island Ferry.A nice extra is their continental breakfast. It was basic, but the bagels were very good and they had hard boild eggs, which I loved! And it lasted until 11am - even on weekends.A big plus is they had free Wi-Fi which was fantastic for checking online for places to eat or the MTA (NYC transit) website.The staff was helpful, but could come off as a little cold at times. They did however suggest a car service to use which worked out fantastic. It was a flat $30 to LaGuardia (not including tip), regardless of rush hour traffic - in case you didn't know, you pay for waiting in traffic while in a cab in NYC.The price seemed comparable to other places nearby. They also appear to have weekend rates around $300ish, so check into it when booking the room. I would definitely recommend this hotel.	
