Sep 17 2008 	Nice Inn Heart of Financial District	I chose this hotel due to its good reviews and its proximity to my business engagement the following morning. Check-in was painless and the room was very comfortable. I was concerned when I saw a dehumidifier chugging away in the hallway near my room on the 6th floor. However, it was a non-issue. I didn't notice any excessive humidity or noise. I would gladly stay here again. PROS: In addition to the nice rooms, directly behind the hotel is a pedestrian-friendly street that is blocked off to traffic. The roadway is full of picnic tables and a neat assortment of restaurants lines the street. CONS: I arrived on a Sunday evening. I took a cab for the &lt;4 mile ride from Penn Station to the hotel. I assumed at 9PM on a Sunday night it would be a relatively quick cab ride. However, traffic was so horrendous it took more than an hour ($30!) to reach the hotel. In addition, the hotel is tucked discreetly between non-descript buildings on a narrow one-way street, so it was a challenge for the cab driver to find the place. I was glad I had printed a mapquest.com map for him to use.For my return trip to Penn station the next afternoon, I opted for the subway and the trip was a mere 20 mins.	
