Aug 5 2008	Nice stay	We found this hotel through travelocity and then read the reviews on tripdavisor. We stayed for a long weekend (Friday through Monday) and found that the rates were much cheaper than other NYC hotels. Check In/Check Out: Both were easy and quick. We had no problems with having three people in the room and the process took minutes. When we checked out we were able to store our luggage in the hotel so that we didn't have to drag it around with us as we spent the day in the city. Room: The room was very nice, clean and quiet. Two comfortable double beds and really nice pillows. The bathroom was clean and had a nice shower with good water pressure. We did find that the room had a bit of a musty smell to it, but it wasn't a huge deal. Breakfast: The breakfast was good but very basic. It had bagels, cereal and a few pastries. Definitely enough to start us on our day, but if you usually have a big, full breakfast this might not be the best place for you. Surrounding area: The area is very quiet on weekends with few people or cars. This has its pros and cons in that everything closes down early on the weekend or never opens at all (when I checked in at 10 I went to find some food and nothing was open, also when we decided to go out for drinks there was little to choose from). But it also means that you don't have street noise when you sleep, which is nice after a long day of trekking around the city. However, it would have been nice to have been more conveniently located as we were required to either subway or cab into midtown everyday. Service: I thought the front desk service was great. The woman who worked there was extremely friendly, calling cabs for us and walking outside with us to make sure we can find them, storing our luggage for us and basically just being friendly. However, we did have a bit of a maintenance issue that I don't believe was idealy handled. When we came home on our second day of staying at the WSI we found that our toilet didn'