Jul 22 2008 	Great Little Inn Tucked Away in the Financial District	We just returned from a weekend stay in NYC at the Wall Street Inn. We had never stayed in this part of the city, but as it turned out, it was fine. The subway wasn't too far away, there is some good shopping a few blocks away at Broadway and Courtland (Century 21!!!) and there are a few restaurants nearby. The South Street Seaport was fairly close, which was convenient because we took a CircleLine tour of the waterfalls (recommended!). Also, there is a Duane Reade, a wine shop and a Borders pretty close by too. We had a wonderful dinner one night at Fraunces Tavern (historical tavern where General Washington bade farewell to his officers after the Revolutionary War), which was just a block from our hotel. If going uptown--it's the 1, 2, or 3, J, M, Z or A, C, E trains--BUT allow plenty of time, because you have a ways to go to get to the theatre district or midtown.Now, about the hotel itself--imagine a smallish, quaint, boutique-type hotel. Lovely lobby, helpful staff, and a good continental breakfast offered each morning until 11:00 am (bagels, sweet rolls, boiled eggs, cereal, fruit, milk, juice, coffee, tea). The rooms are a decent size--we had a double/double and had plenty of room. The beds are comfortable, and the bathroom is spacious and pretty--marble everywhere, a makeup mirror, a hairdryer and telephone. The bath towels were very white and plush (but not too plush) and the bathroom amenities were plentiful--soap, shampoo, conditioner, lotion, mending kit, shower cap and breath mints. We had a flat-screen television and a mini-fridge (great for holding the leftover Carnegie deli cheesecake!). The hotel is quiet at night--we didn't hear any street noise whatsoever. The rooms were cleaned thoroughly during our stay and chocolates put at our bedside each night. Also, a real plus was that our room was ready--even though we arrived at 9:00 am! They also store your luggage for free, should you need it.All in all, a wonderful stay and I will be back to visit the Wall Street Inn!	
