Nov 25 2007 	Lovely little hotel	I stayed in this hotel for 6 nights with my partner while attending a conference. Upon arrival, staff were very friendly and chatted with us as we checked in. They then gave us our key and told us how to find our room.Location:The hotel is on a small, one way street right off Wall Street. During the weekdays, there were a number of business people floating around, particularly during lunchtime. It is a short walk to Ground zero and battery park and should you wish to go further, Wall Street station is up the top of William Street. The subway was very efficient, both with cost and time, and easy to use. The best feature of the location was at night, when it was considerably more quiet than uptown areas, allowing us to relax after busy days of sightseeing and shopping. Although there were few people around at night, at no time did we feel unsafe.Room:The room itself was at the back of the hotel, facing onto Stone Street which has a very popular (and noisy) restaurant. Luckily we were a few levels up and weren't disturbed by the noise. Rooms at the back (or front) of the hotel (rooms ending in 01 or 08) are smaller than the ones on the side, but they do have a window, which, I think, was a fair trade off. The bathroom was also smallish, but I suppose I was expecting that since we were in New York. Bathroom:The main problem was that the bathroom has only a sheer curtain over the window, and at night I'm sure that people in the building next door can see right in when you take a shower with the light on. The water pressure was also a bit low, but passable.Airconditioning:It seems that a few reviewers have mentioned problems with the rooms being either too cold or too hot. Well, we had both! The airconditioner seemed to have some really weird cycle where it would go from being far too cold to being, really, quite too warm. This meant that we were constantly pulling up the covers and then throwing them off all night. The thermostat didn't seem to be easily adjusted. Pressing the warmer and cooler buttons didn't change the temperature displayed on the thermostat and the room didn't feel like the temperature it displayed either... weird. On top, the unit was very noisy (think airplane), although that didn't bother me too much since it drowned out the noise of my boyfriend snoring :P But overall, a good room:Positives of the room included a safe, iron and board, hairdryer, new carpeting and bathroom and everything was spotless. The bed was really comfortable with down pillows.Breakfast:Breakfast is served between 7am and 11am each morning and included a variety of cereals (accommodates both kids and adults) with full cream and light milk, pastries (chocolate, jam etc), fruit, bagels and toast with various spreads and tea, coffee and hot chocolate. The tea and coffee facilites are avilable all day and they provide cups with lids if you want to take it with you.Staff:Whenever we encountered the staff, they were friendly and helpful. We got the concierge to book a taxi for us the day we left. He let us know when it arrived and went out with us to point it out (there were a few there).Fantastic overall - if we were to go to New York again (and could get a reasonable price), we would definitely stay here.	
