Jul 5 2006 	Unique in NYC !	The trip from Newark Airport via airport van was a grizzily -- long queues of traffic at the tunnel and into the city. Pulling up to the Wall Stree Inn --located on a quiet street-- was a positive relief ! Entering the quiet lobby --and finding the reservation for the room to be 'in order'-- was yet better.A single elevator goes from the lobby to one of seven floors, with about six rooms to a floor. For New York City, Wall Street Inn is unusually small, as well as quiet. On the seventh floor, some of the rooms have sittiing areas -- and this provides space for in-room dining. Carry-out menus are in the room (the hotel serves continential breakfast only, which is included in the price). The continental breakfast is more than adequate -- with bagels, cream cheese, cereal, juice, coffee/tea. Also, on weeek-ends breakfast service runs until 10:30 am (welcome span of time !).Downtown New York --the location of the Wall Street Inn-- is the oldest region of New York City, and on a week-end especially, the foot and street traffic are low. Also, the area is free-er of tourism than other areas of NYC. Makes for a nice stay.For the return to Newark airport (as well as other airports), the reception desk will arrange for a private auto -- worth the extra cost over the van service !If lookiing for a small, quiet, non-commercial hotel in New York City, Wall Street Inn is a great choice !	
