May 30 2006	Perfect for a weekend stay	I stayed at the Wall Street Inn during my weekend trip to Manhattan, and it was an outstanding experience overall. The room prices were amazing for the location, and the room was clean and comfortable. It is a bit out of the way and quiet, but that was a welcomed departure for the city.The free internet connection was a huge plus for me as well, as I like to always be connected, and many hotels charge a fortune for that or don't have high-speed connections at all.The only downside during my stay was that the subways in that area of lower manhattan were running very poorly (if at all) on the weekends -- especially at night. There is a lot of construction going on. Also, for some reason it was difficult for cabs to locate the hotel since there are so many blocked roads around Wall street. However, this was not too much of a problem as I became familiar with the area very easily and was able to walk the few blocks if necessary. Just be aware that if you want to use the subway stations in the area that weekend routes are modified or inactive.	
